From 25fdf36988faf91885a84107873843d33863ad28 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mykola Lysenko <mykolal@meta.com>
Date: Thu, 18 Jun 2026 09:28:46 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] selftests/bpf: veristat: preserve zero max_entries for
 percpu cgroup storage

fixup_obj_maps() avoids forcing max_entries for cgroup storage maps
because those map types require max_entries == 0.
BPF_MAP_TYPE_PERCPU_CGROUP_STORAGE has the same requirement, but was not
in the exclusion list.

Keep percpu cgroup storage maps with their original max_entries value so
standalone veristat runs do not turn otherwise valid selftest objects into
BPF_MAP_CREATE -EINVAL failures.

Signed-off-by: Mykola Lysenko <mykolal@meta.com>
---
 tools/testing/selftests/bpf/veristat.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/tools/testing/selftests/bpf/veristat.c b/tools/testing/selftests/bpf/veristat.c
index a7db6f04f7e1..43d885b407dc 100644
--- a/tools/testing/selftests/bpf/veristat.c
+++ b/tools/testing/selftests/bpf/veristat.c
@@ -1253,6 +1253,7 @@ static void fixup_obj_maps(struct bpf_object *obj)
 		case BPF_MAP_TYPE_INODE_STORAGE:
 		case BPF_MAP_TYPE_CGROUP_STORAGE:
 		case BPF_MAP_TYPE_CGRP_STORAGE:
+		case BPF_MAP_TYPE_PERCPU_CGROUP_STORAGE:
 		case BPF_MAP_TYPE_STRUCT_OPS:
 			break;
 		default:
